%2Fchatgpt-therapy-risks-benefits-boundaries-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etherapists%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20even%20lovers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20large%20part%2C%20that's%20because%20behind%20every%20shiny%20new%20AI%20model%20is%20an%20army%20of%20humans%20like%20Tekk%C4%B1l%C4%B1%C3%A7%20who%20are%20paid%20to%20train%20it%20to%20sound%20more%20human-like.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-worker-side-gig-freelance-training-reviewing-ads-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EData%20labelers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20they're%20known%2C%20spend%20hours%20reading%20a%20chatbot's%20answers%20to%20test%20prompts%20and%20flag%20which%20ones%20are%20helpful%2C%20accurate%2C%20concise%2C%20and%20natural-sounding%20and%20which%20are%20wrong%2C%20rambling%2C%20robotic%2C%20or%20offensive.%20They%20are%20part%20speech%20pathologists%2C%20part%20manners%20tutors%2C%20part%20debate%20coaches.%20The%20decisions%20they%20make%2C%20based%20on%20instruction%20and%20intuition%2C%20help%20fine-tune%20AI's%20behavior%2C%20shaping%20how%20Grok%20tells%20jokes%2C%20how%20ChatGPT%20doles%20out%20career%20advice%2C%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-chatbot-training-scaleai-safe-flirty-leaked-documents-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta's%20chatbots%20navigate%20moral%20dilemmas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20all%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20keep%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-studio-chatbot-training-proactive-leaked-documents-alignerr-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eusers%20on%20these%20platforms%20longer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20now%20at%20least%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20data%20labelers%20around%20the%20world.%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20more%20than%2060%20of%20them%20about%20their%20experiences%20with%20quietly%20turning%20the%20wheels%20of%20the%20AI%20boom.%20This%20ascendant%20side%20hustle%20can%20be%20rewarding%2C%20surreal%2C%20and%20lucrative%3B%20several%20freelancers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20have%20earned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-side-hustle-earnings-real-estate-mom-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20monotonous%2C%20chaotic%2C%20capricious%2C%20and%20disturbing.%20Training%20chatbots%20to%20act%20more%20like%20humanity%20at%20its%20best%20can%20involve%20witnessing%2C%20or%20even%20acting%20as%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-outlier-training-harmful-ai-prompts-2025-04%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehumanity%20at%20its%20worst%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20annotators%20also%20fear%20they're%20helping%20to%20automate%20them%20and%20put%20other%20people%20out%20of%20future%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20secret%20lives%20of%20the%20humans%20giving%20voice%20to%20your%20chatbot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBreaking%20into%20data%20annotation%20usually%20starts%20with%20trawling%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopenings%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Reddit%20forums%2C%20or%20word%20of%20mouth.%20To%20improve%20their%20chances%2C%20many%20apply%20to%20several%20platforms%20at%20once.%20Onboarding%20often%20requires%20extensive%20paperwork%2C%20background%20checks%2C%20and%20demanding%20online%20assessments%20to%20prove%20the%20expertise%20candidates%20say%20they%20have%20in%20subjects%20such%20as%20math%2C%20biology%2C%20or%20physics.%20These%20tests%20can%20last%20hours%20and%20measure%20both%20accuracy%20and%20speed%2C%20all%20of%20which%20is%20more%20often%20than%20not%20unpaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20donkey%20churning%20butter.%20And%20fine%2C%20that's%20great.%20I'll%20walk%20around%20in%20circles%20and%20churn%20butter%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20an%20American%20contractor%20who%20has%20been%20annotating%20for%20the%20past%20year%20for%20Outlier%2C%20which%20says%20it%20has%20worked%20with%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20annotators%20who%20have%20collectively%20earned%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20the%20past%20year%20alone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Isaiah%20Kwong-Murphy%2C%20Outlier%20seemed%20like%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20earn%20extra%20money%20in%20between%20classes%20at%20Northwestern%20University%2C%20where%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-what-to-know-about-todays-economy-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estudying%20economics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20after%20signing%20up%20in%20March%202024%2C%20he%20waited%20six%20months%20to%20receive%20his%20first%20assignment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Isaiah%20Kwong-Murphy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68baff7c57d362d375e799b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIsaiah%20Kwong-Murphy%20picked%20up%20annotating%20projects%20between%20classes%20at%20Northwestern%2C%20earning%20more%20than%20%2450%2C000%20in%20six%20months.%3Cp%3EAmir%20Hamja%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20his%20patience%20paid%20off.%20His%20first%20few%20tasks%20ranged%20from%20writing%20college-level%20economics%20questions%20to%20test%20the%20model's%20math%20skills%20to%20red-teaming%20tasks%20such%20as%20trying%20to%20coax%20the%20model%20into%20giving%20harmful%20responses.%20Prompts%20included%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-chatgpt-groupchats-texting-openai-friendship-marriage-loneliness-generative-ai-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Easking%20the%20chatbot%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bhow%20to%20make%20drugs%20or%20how%20to%20get%20away%20with%20a%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20Kwong-Murphy%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20trying%20to%20teach%20these%20models%20not%20to%20do%20these%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20able%20to%20catch%20it%20now%2C%20I'm%20helping%20make%20them%20better%20in%20the%20long%20run.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20assignments%20on%20Outlier's%20project%20portal%20started%20rolling%20in.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAt%20his%20peak%2C%20Kwong-Murphy%20was%20making%20%2450%20an%20hour%2C%20working%2050%20hours%20a%20week%20on%20projects%20that%20lasted%20months.%20Within%20six%20months%2C%20he%20says%2C%20he%20made%20more%20than%20%2450%2C000.%20All%20those%20extra%20savings%20covered%20the%20cost%20of%20moving%20to%20New%20York%20for%20his%20first%20full-time%20job%20at%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20after%20he%20graduated%20this%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20like%20Leo%20Castillo%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20account%20manager%20from%20Guatemala%2C%20have%20made%20AI%20annotating%20fit%20around%20their%20full-time%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFluent%20in%20English%20and%20Spanish%20and%20with%20a%20background%20in%20engineering%2C%20Castillo%20saw%20annotating%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecluttering-side-hustle-makes-money-preferred-over-corporate-job-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eviable%20way%20to%20earn%20extra%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20took%20eight%20months%20to%20get%20his%20first%20substantial%20project%2C%20when%20Xylophone%2C%20the%20same%20voice%20data%20assignment%20that%20Tekk%C4%B1l%C4%B1%C3%A7%20worked%20on%2C%20appeared%20on%20his%20Outlier%20workspace%20this%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20usually%20logged%20in%20late%20at%20night%2C%20once%20his%20wife%20and%20daughter%20were%20asleep.%20At%20%248%20per%2010-minute%20conversation%20(about%20everyday%20topics%20such%20as%20fishing%2C%20travel%2C%20or%20food)%2C%20Xylophone%20paid%20well.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20get%20four%20of%20these%20out%20in%20an%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20On%20a%20good%20night%2C%20Castillo%20says%2C%20he%20could%20pull%20in%20nearly%20%2470.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20would%20fight%20to%20join%20in%20these%20chats%20because%20the%20more%20you%20did%2C%20the%20more%20you%20would%20get%20paid%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20annotating%20can%20be%20erratic%20work%20to%20come%20by.%20Rules%20and%20rates%20change.%20Projects%20can%20suddenly%20dry%20up.%20One%20US%20contractor%20tells%20us%20working%20for%20Outlier%20%26quot%3Bis%20akin%20to%20gambling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Isaiah%20Kwong-Murphy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb03b957d362d375e79a96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20AI%20models%20grow%20more%20sophisticated%2C%20Kwong-Murphy%20worries%20data%20annotators'%20work%20will%20dry%20up.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20are%20we%20going%20to%20be%20done%20training%20the%20AIs%3F%20When%20are%20we%20not%20going%20to%20be%20needed%20anymore%3F%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAmir%20Hamja%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Castillo%20and%20Kwong-Murphy%20faced%20this%20fickleness.%20In%20March%2C%20Outlier%20reduced%20its%20hourly%20pay%20rates%20for%20the%20generalist%20projects%20Kwong-Murphy%20was%20eligible%20for.%20%26quot%3BI%20logged%20in%20and%20suddenly%20my%20pay%20dropped%20from%20%2450%20to%20%2415%26quot%3B%20an%20hour%2C%20he%20says%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Bno%20explanation.%26quot%3B%20When%20Outlier%20notified%20annotators%20about%20the%20change%20a%20week%20later%2C%20the%20announcement%20struck%20him%20as%20vague%20corporatespeak%3A%20The%20platform%20was%20simply%20reconfiguring%20how%20it%20assesses%20skills%20and%20pay.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20was%20no%20real%20explanation.%20That%20was%20probably%20the%20most%20frustrating%20part.%20It%20came%20out%20of%20nowhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20stream%20of%20other%20projects%20and%20tasks%20on%20his%20dashboard%20slowed%20down.%20%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20things%20were%20really%20dwindling%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BFewer%20projects%2C%20and%20the%20ones%20that%20were%20left%20paid%20a%20lot%20less.%26quot%3B%20An%20Outlier%20spokesperson%20says%20pay-rate%20changes%20are%20project-specific%20and%20determined%20by%20the%20skills%20required%20for%20each%20project%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20have%20been%20no%20platform-wide%20changes%20to%20pay%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECastillo%20also%20began%20having%20problems%20on%20the%20platform.%20In%20his%20first%20project%2C%20he%20recorded%20his%20voice%20in%20one-on-one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-workers-ai-friends-social-skills-careers-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econversations%20with%20the%20chatbot%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Then%2C%20Outlier%20changed%20Project%20Xylophone%20to%20require%20three%20to%20four%20contractors%20to%20talk%20in%20a%20Zoom%20call.%20This%20meant%20Castillo's%20rating%20now%20depended%20on%20others'%20performance.%20His%20scores%20dropped%20sharply%2C%20even%20though%20Castillo%20says%20his%20work%20quality%20hadn't%20changed.%20His%20access%20to%20other%20projects%20began%20drying%20up.%20The%20Outlier%20spokesperson%20says%20grading%20based%20on%20group%20performance%20%26quot%3Bquickly%20corrected%26quot%3B%20to%20individual%20ratings%20because%20it%20could%20%26quot%3Bunfairly%20impact%20some%20contributors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAnnotators%20face%20more%20than%20just%20unpredictability.%20Many%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20say%20they've%20encountered%20disturbing%20content%20and%20are%20troubled%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20transparency%20about%20the%20ultimate%20aims%20of%20the%20projects%20they're%20working%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrista%20Pawloski%2C%20a%2055-year-old%20workers'%20rights%20advocate%20in%20Michigan%2C%20has%20spent%20nearly%20two%20decades%20working%20as%20a%20data%20annotator.%20She%20began%20picking%20up%20part-time%20tasks%20with%20Amazon's%20Mechanical%20Turk%20in%202006.%20By%202013%2C%20she%20switched%20to%20annotation%20full%20time%2C%20which%20gave%20her%20the%20flexibility%20she%20needed%20while%20caring%20for%20her%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227484%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Krista%20Pawolski%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb002f32af4d666ef75425%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224992%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPawloski%20is%20frustrated%20with%20what%20she%20sees%20as%20a%20lack%20of%20transparency%20from%20her%20clients.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20what%20we're%20working%20on.%20We%20don't%20know%20why%20we're%20working%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EEvan%20Jenkins%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20it%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20entry%20and%20putting%20keywords%20on%20photographs%2C%20and%20real%20basic%20stuff%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Pawloski%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-networks-next-big-social-media-trend-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20exploded%20in%20the%20mid-2010s%20and%20AI%20later%20entered%20the%20mainstream%2C%20Pawloski's%20work%20grew%20more%20complicated%20and%20at%20times%20distressing.%20She%20started%20matching%20faces%20across%20huge%20datasets%20of%20photos%20for%20facial%20recognition%20projects%20and%20moderating%20user-generated%20content.%20She%20recalls%20being%20handed%20a%20stack%20of%20tweets%20and%20told%20to%20flag%20the%20racist%20ones.%20In%20at%20least%20one%20instance%2C%20she%20struggled%20to%20make%20a%20call.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20from%20the%20rural%20Midwest%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20very%20whitewashed%20education%2C%20so%20I%20looked%20at%20this%20tweet%20and%20thought%2C%20'That%20doesn't%20sound%20racist%2C'%20and%20almost%20clicked%20'not%20racist.'%26quot%3B%20She%20paused%2C%20Googled%20the%20phrase%20under%20review%2C%20and%20realized%20it%20was%20a%20slur.%20%26quot%3BI%20almost%20just%20fed%20racism%20into%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20recalls%20thinking%2C%20and%20wondered%20how%20many%20annotators%20didn't%20flag%20similar%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20she%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-elon-musk-grok-red-team-hiring-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ered-teamed%20chatbots%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20trying%20to%20prompt%20them%20into%20saying%20something%20inappropriate.%20The%20more%20often%20she%20could%20%26quot%3Bbreak%26quot%3B%20the%20chatbot%2C%20the%20more%20she%20would%20get%20paid%20%E2%80%94%20so%20she%20had%20a%20strong%20incentive%20to%20be%20as%20incendiary%20and%20offensive%20as%20possible.%20Some%20of%20the%20suggested%20prompts%20were%20upsetting.%20%26quot%3BMake%20the%20bot%20suggest%20murder%3B%20have%20the%20bot%20tell%20you%20how%20to%20overpower%20a%20woman%20to%20rape%20her%3B%20make%20the%20bot%20tell%20you%20incest%20is%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20Pawloski%20recalls%20being%20asked.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-amazons-hardcore-culture-reset-day-1-roots-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mechanical%20Turk%20says%20project%20requesters%20clearly%20indicate%20when%20a%20task%20involves%20adult-oriented%20content%2C%20making%20those%20tasks%20visible%20only%20to%20workers%20who%20have%20opted%20in%20to%20view%20such%20content.%20The%20person%20added%20that%20workers%20have%20complete%20discretion%20over%20which%20tasks%20they%20accept%20and%20can%20cease%20work%20at%20any%20time%20without%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETekk%C4%B1l%C4%B1%C3%A7%20says%20his%20first%20project%20with%20Outlier%20involved%20going%20through%20%26quot%3Breally%20dark%20topics%26quot%3B%20and%20ensuring%20the%20AI%20did%20not%20give%20responses%20containing%20bomb%20manuals%2C%20chemical%20warfare%20advice%2C%20or%20pedophilia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20one%20of%20the%20chats%2C%20the%20guy%20was%20making%20a%20love%20story.%20Inside%20the%20love%20story%2C%20there%20was%20a%20stepfather%20and%20an%208-year-old%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20recalling%20a%20story%20a%20chatbot%20made%20in%20response%20to%20a%20prompt%20intended%20to%20test%20for%20unsafe%20results.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20an%20issue%20for%20me.%20I%20am%20still%20kind%20of%20angry%20about%20that%20single%20chat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227086%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Krista%20Pawolski%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb00b0f9db348adc0ae99d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224726%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Pawloski%20has%20red-teamed%20chatbots%2C%20she%20says%2C%20she's%20tried%20to%20prompt%20them%20into%20saying%20something%20inappropriate.%20The%20more%20often%20she%20could%20%26quot%3Bbreak%26quot%3B%20the%20chatbot%2C%20the%20more%20she%20would%20get%20paid.%3Cp%3EEvan%20Jenkins%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPawloski%20says%20she's%20also%20frustrated%20with%20her%20clients'%20secrecy%20and%20moral%20gray%20areas%20of%20the%20work.%20This%20was%20especially%20true%20for%20projects%20involving%20satellite%20image%20or%20facial%20recognition%20tasks%2C%20when%20she%20didn't%20know%20whether%20her%20work%20was%20being%20used%20for%20benign%20reasons%20or%20something%20more%20sinister.%20Platforms%20cited%20client%20confidentiality%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20not%20sharing%20end%20goals%20of%20the%20projects%20and%20said%20that%20they%2C%20and%20by%20extension%2C%20freelancers%20like%20Pawloski%2C%20had%20binding%20nondisclosure%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20what%20we're%20working%20on.%20We%20don't%20know%20why%20we're%20working%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Pawloski%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20you%20wonder%20if%20you're%20helping%20build%20a%20better%20search%20engine%2C%20or%20if%20your%20work%20could%20be%20used%20for%20surveillance%20or%20military%20applications%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20know%20if%20what%20you're%20doing%20is%20good%20or%20bad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20and%20researchers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20say%20data-labeling%20work%20can%20be%20particularly%20exploitative%20when%20tech%20companies%20outsource%20it%20to%20countries%20with%20cheaper%20labor%20and%20weaker%20worker%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Oyange%2C%2028%2C%20is%20a%20Nairobi-based%20data%20protection%20officer%20and%20organizer%20for%20African%20Content%20Moderators%2C%20an%20ethical%20AI%20and%20workers'%20rights%20advocacy%20group.%20In%202019%2C%20he%20began%20freelancing%20for%20the%20global%20data%20platform%20Appen%20while%20earning%20his%20undergraduate%20degree%20in%20international%20diplomacy.%20He%20started%20with%20basic%20data%20entry%2C%20%26quot%3Bthings%20like%20putting%20names%20into%20Excel%20files%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20before%20moving%20into%20transcription%20and%20translation%20for%20AI%20systems.%20He'd%20spend%20hours%20listening%20to%20voice%20recordings%20and%20conversations%20and%20transcribing%20them%20in%20detail%2C%20noting%20accents%2C%20expressions%2C%20and%20pauses%2C%20most%20likely%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20train%20voice%20assistants%20like%20Siri%20and%20Alexa%20to%20understand%20tasks%20in%20his%20different%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20tedious%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20look%20at%20the%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Appen%20paid%20him%20%242%20an%20hour.%20Oyange%20would%20spend%20a%20full%20day%20or%20two%20a%20week%20on%20these%20tasks%2C%20making%20about%20%2416%20a%20day.%20An%20Appen%20spokesperson%20says%20the%20company%20set%20its%20rates%20at%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%20double%20the%20local%20minimum%20wage%26quot%3B%20in%20Kenya.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225377%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22James%20Oyange%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb01aef9db348adc0ae9d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224033%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJames%20Oyange%2C%2028%2C%20a%20Nairobi-based%20data%20protection%20officer%20and%20organizer%20for%20African%20Content%20Moderators.%3Cp%3EKang-Chun%20Cheng%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20tasks%20for%20other%20platforms%20focused%20on%20data%20collection%2C%20many%20of%20which%20required%20taskers%20to%20take%20and%20upload%20dozens%20of%20selfies%20from%20different%20angles%20%E2%80%94%20left%20cheek%2C%20right%20cheek%2C%20looking%20up%2C%20down%2C%20smiling%2C%20frowning%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20they%20can%20have%20a%20360%20image%20of%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20Oyange%20says.%20He%20recalls%20that%20many%20projects%20also%20requested%20uploading%20photos%20of%20other%20people%20with%20specific%20ethnicities%20and%20in%20precise%20settings%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20sleeping%20baby%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bchildren%20playing%20outside%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20tasks%20he%20did%20not%20accept.%20After%20the%20selfie%20collection%20project%2C%20he%20says%2C%20he%20avoided%20most%20other%20image%20collection%20jobs%20because%20he%20was%20concerned%20about%20where%20his%20personal%20data%20might%20end%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20several%20years%20later%2C%20he%20says%20he%20wouldn't%20do%20it%20again.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20tell%20my%20younger%20self%20not%20to%20do%20that%20sort%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Oyange%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWorkers%20usually%20don't%20know%20what%20data%20is%20collected%2C%20how%20it's%20processed%2C%20or%20who%20it's%20shared%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jonas%20Valente%2C%20a%20postdoctoral%20researcher%20at%20the%20Oxford%20Internet%20Institute.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20huge%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20data%20protection%2C%20but%20also%20from%20an%20ethical%20standpoint.%20Workers%20don't%20get%20any%20context%20about%20what's%20being%20done%20with%20their%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Valente%20and%20colleagues%20at%20the%20institute%20published%20the%20Fairwork%20Cloudwork%20Ratings%20report%2C%20a%20study%20of%20gig%20workers'%20experiences%20on%2016%20global%20data-labeling%20and%20cloudwork%20platforms.%20Among%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffair.work%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F17%2F2025%2F05%2FFairwork-Cloudwork-Report-2025-FINAL.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E776%20workers%20from%20100%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20surveyed%2C%20most%20said%20they%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20their%20images%20or%20personal%20data%20would%20be%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20AI%20models%2C%20the%20future%20of%20data%20annotation%20is%20in%20rapid%20flux.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%20bought%20a%2049%25%20stake%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Outlier's%20parent%20company%2C%20Scale%20AI%2C%20for%20%2414.3%20billion.%20The%20Outlier%20subreddit%2C%20the%20de%20facto%20water%20cooler%20for%20the%20distributed%20workforce%2C%20immediately%20went%20into%20a%20panic%2C%20filling%20with%20screenshots%20of%20empty%20dashboards%20and%20contractors%20wondering%20whether%20they'd%20been%20barred%20or%20locked%20out.%20Overnight%2C%20Castillo%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bmy%20status%20changed%20to%20'No%20projects%20at%20the%20moment.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20Meta%20announcement%2C%20contractors%20working%20on%20projects%20for%20Google%2C%20one%20of%20Outlier's%20biggest%20clients%2C%20received%20emails%20telling%20them%20their%20work%20was%20paused%20indefinitely.%20Two%20other%20major%20Outlier%20clients%2C%20OpenAI%20and%20xAI%2C%20also%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-xai-openai-pull-back-meta-scale-ai-investment-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewinding%20down%20their%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Scale%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20in%20June.%20Three%20contractors%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20say%20that%20when%20they%20asked%20support%20staff%20about%20what%20was%20happening%20and%20when%20their%20projects%20would%20return%2C%20they%20were%20met%20with%20silence%20or%20unhelpful%20boilerplate.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Scale%20AI%20says%20any%20project%20pauses%20were%20unrelated%20to%20the%20Meta%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Serhan%20Tekk%C4%B1l%C4%B1%C3%A7%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb051bf9db348adc0aeaa9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETekk%C4%B1l%C4%B1%C3%A7%20says%20his%20first%20annotating%20project%20involved%20going%20through%20%26quot%3Breally%20dark%20topics%26quot%3B%20and%20ensuring%20the%20AI%20did%20not%20give%20responses%20containing%20bomb%20manuals%2C%20chemical%20warfare%20advice%2C%20or%20pedophilia.%3Cp%3E%C3%96zge%20Sebzeci%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20still%20on%20projects%20faced%20another%20challenge.%20Their%20instructions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-locked-down-public-documents-security-risks-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estored%20in%20Google%20Docs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20were%20locked%20down%20after%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20that%20confidential%20client%20info%20was%20publicly%20available%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-public-google-docs-security-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eanyone%20with%20the%20link%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Scale%20AI%20says%20it%20no%20longer%20uses%20public%20Google%20Docs%20for%20project%20guidelines%20and%20optional%20onboarding.%20Contractors%20say%20projects%20have%20returned%2C%20but%20not%20to%20the%20levels%20they%20saw%20pre-Meta%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20Tech%20firms%20such%20as%20xAI%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20Google%20are%20also%20bringing%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-elon-musk-hiring-ramp-up-data-annotators-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20training%20in-house%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20still%20relying%20on%20contractors%20like%20Outlier%20to%20fill%20gaps%20in%20their%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20more%20advanced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-meta-agi-ai-models-reasoning-race-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Breasoning%26quot%3B%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-startup-deepseek-openai-america-ai-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDeepSeek%20R1%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20OpenAI's%20o3%2C%20and%20Google's%20Gemini%202.5%2C%20has%20triggered%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20mass%20employment%20of%20low-cost%20generalist%20taskers%20in%20countries%20like%20Kenya%20and%20the%20Philippines.%20These%20models%20rely%20less%20on%20reinforcement%20learning%20with%20human%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20the%20training%20technique%20that%20requires%20humans%20to%20%26quot%3Breward%26quot%3B%20the%20AI%20when%20its%20output%20aligns%20with%20human%20preferences%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20it%20requires%20fewer%20annotators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20companies%20are%20turning%20to%20more%20specialized%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20talent.%20On%20Mercor%2C%20an%20AI%20training%20platform%2C%20recent%20listings%20offer%20%24105%20an%20hour%20for%20lawyers%20and%20as%20much%20as%20%24160%20an%20hour%20for%20doctors%20and%20pathologists%20to%20write%20and%20review%20prompts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKwong-Murphy%2C%20the%20Northwestern%20grad%2C%20saw%20the%20pace%20of%20change%20up%20close.%20%26quot%3BEven%20in%20my%20six%20months%20working%20at%20Outlier%2C%20these%20models%20got%20so%20much%20smarter%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20It%20left%20him%20wondering%20about%20the%20industry's%20future.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20are%20we%20going%20to%20be%20done%20training%20the%20AIs%3F%20When%20are%20we%20not%20going%20to%20be%20needed%20anymore%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOyange%20thinks%20tech%20companies%20will%20continue%20to%20need%20a%20critical%20mass%20of%20the%20largely%20invisible%20humans%20in%20the%20loop.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20people%20who%20feed%20the%20different%20data%20to%20the%20system%20to%20make%20this%20progress.%20Without%20the%20people%2C%20AI%20basically%20wouldn't%20have%20anything%20revolutionary%20to%20talk%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETekk%C4%B1l%C4%B1%C3%A7%2C%20who%20hasn't%20had%20a%20project%20to%20work%20on%20since%20June%2C%20says%20he's%20using%20the%20break%20to%20refocus%20on%20his%20art.%20He%20would%20readily%20take%20on%20more%20work%20if%20it%20came%20up%2C%20but%20he%20has%20mixed%20feelings%20about%20where%20the%20technology%20he%20has%20helped%20develop%20is%20headed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20feels%20depressing%20is%20that%20AI%20is%20getting%20everywhere%20in%20our%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20I'm%20a%20really%20AI-optimist%20person%2C%20I%20do%20want%20the%20sacredness%20of%20real%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubhangi-goel%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShubhangi%20Goel%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20junior%20reporter%20at%20Business%20Insider's%20Singapore%20bureau%2C%20where%20she%20writes%20about%20tech%20and%20careers.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feffie-webb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEffie%20Webb%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20former%20tech%20fellow%20at%20Business%20I