0shared%20footage%20of%20the%20interaction%20on%20social%20media%2C%20where%20one%20clip%20gained%20nearly%2053%20million%20views.%20The%20phrase%20%26quot%3BPhillies%20Karen%26quot%3B%20topped%20Google%20Trends%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20a%20stadium%20employee%20gifted%20the%20boy%20and%20his%20sister%20goody%20bags%20during%20the%20game.%20Additionally%2C%20Harrison%20Bader%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Philadelphia%20Phillies%20player%20who%20hit%20the%20home%20run%20%E2%80%94%20met%20the%20family%20after%20the%20game%20and%20gifted%20the%20boy%20a%20bat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20viral%20stadium%20fan%20moment%20happened%20last%20month%20at%20the%20US%20Open%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20match%20between%20Russia's%20Karen%20Khachanov%20and%20Poland's%20Kamil%20Majchrzak%20in%20August%2C%20Majchrzak%20stayed%20near%20the%20court%20and%20signed%20mementos%20for%20crowd%20members.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20Majchrzak%20removed%20his%20hat%20and%20appeared%20to%20give%20it%20to%20a%20nearby%20boy%2C%20but%20a%20man%20suddenly%20reached%20out%20and%20nabbed%20it.%20Clips%20of%20the%20interaction%20were%20shared%20online%2C%20where%20one%20received%20over%2024%20million%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20users%20identified%20the%20man%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-open-coldplay-kiss-cam-ceos-kamil-majchrzak-piotr-szczerek-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPiotr%20Szczerek%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Polish%20chief%20executive.%20After%20some%20social%20media%20users%20criticized%20Szczerek's%20behavior%2C%20he%20apologized%20on%20Facebook%20in%20September%2C%20saying%20he%20had%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20mistake%26quot%3B%20and%20assumed%20the%20tennis%20player%20had%20passed%20him%20the%20hat.%20Majchrzak%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20later%20met%20the%20boy%20in%20person%20to%20gift%20him%20merch%20and%20pose%20for%20photos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20perhaps%20most%20fa